I think we leak `cper_event`? I can't see the corresponding free from a brief scan.

I've developed a pattern for avoiding the leak, and `reinterpret_cast<>()`, while staying inside the boundaries of the language. The trick is to use "placement new".

Assuming we have:

```
constexpr size_t msgDataLen = sizeof(pldm_platform_cper_event) + cperEventDateSize;
```

then for the heap, as we need in this case:

```
#include <memory>

auto msgData = std::make_unique<unsigned char[]>(msgDataLen);
auto msg = new (msgData.get()) pldm_platform_cper_event;
...
```

For the stack it is:

```
alignas(platform_cper_event) unsigned char msgData[msgDataLen];
auto msg = new (msgData) pldm_platform_cper_event;
...
```

Destructors need to be invoked explicitly for placement new, but as we're using POD types generally we can ignore that and let them go out of scope without running the destructor.
